[SN]TITLE[SN]
Accrington Stanley 2-2 Stevenage

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Chris Beardsley rescued a point for play-off chasers Stevenage in the final minute against 10-man Accrington.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Nicky Hunt was dismissed in the first minute for Accrington before the home side went ahead through Sean Maguire.
Stevenage equalised when Simon Walton converted from the spot after Lloyd Jones handled in the area.
Maguire fired in his second to give Stanley the lead again, but it was heartbreak for Accrington as Beardsley hooked in to level late on.
Accrington sit in 17th, with their place in League Two safe with only two games remaining.
Stevenage are in sixth position, and look likely for a play-off place as eighth-placed Luton are four points behind.
Stevenage boss Graham Westley told BBC Three Counties Radio:
